    <p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Hot Shot Loading And Its Advantage Over The Conventional One</strong>
	</p>
    <p class="g-font-size-18--xs">With the increasing competition in the carrier service, the truck operators are finding it a little 
    hard to get a good income from the dispatching services. But when you can have hot shot loads, you may be able to earn a little more 
    but the quality of dispatch is also needed to be high and you need to be accurate on time. The advantage with the hot shot load is 
    that you can easily make use of only one truck in combination with several carriers to generate more income while spending lesser 
    amount of money on the fuel. There are some companies that might provide you with hot shot loads at some commission charges but the 
    profit you earn with these more than makes up for it.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">
	To help you explore more about the hot shot load, here are some of the advantages that you have with the hot shot service:
	<ul>
		<li >
			With a hot shot loading service, you can make use of a single truck in association with two or three trailers which costs you 
			lesser than when you opt for regular dispatching system for which you require three trucks and trailers. Thus, it makes things 
			so very easy for you in case you are looking to start a new carrier service as you need to invest lesser amount of money in your 
			business.
		</li>
		<li >
			Second advantage of this service is the reduced per mile charge. Thus, there is substantial increase in your profits making it a 
			better deal for you. At the same time, it also results in expedite delivery of the loads to destination.
		</li>
		<li >
			With the hot shot niche, you are going to get most of the work in your region as it is tougher to carry heavy weight to longer 
			distances. Thus, it is very good from personal and family point of view as you can give them more time
		</li>
	</ul>
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>How to Work Systematically With a Trucking Dispatcher for Your Freight</strong>
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">In order to ship the goods by road, you need to rely on the trucking services. There are lots of players' 
	available providing quality services. If you are also looking for one then you need to understand few important factors that will decide 
	the quality of service you are going to get.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Apart from the quality service, you need to look for the below mentioned important factors:</strong>
		<ul>
			<li >
				Reliability
			</li>
			<li >
				Speed of operation
			</li>
			<li >
				Cost
			</li>
			<li >
				Coverage
			</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">If you are planning to ship some goods, your first priority would always be the time factor. To meet your 
	client's requirement and to get a good value for your money, prepare a questionnaire. All the formalities can be sorted out with a simple 
	interview with the trucking dispatcher.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">Make sure you have listed out the points you want to clarify with the trucking dispatcher. Take some time 
	to discuss in detail well in advance.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>You can add the following factors for your discussion:</strong>
		<ul>
			<li >
				Does the trucking service provider guarantee the shipping delivery time? In case of delays what are his contingency plans? 
				What if the delay happens due to driver's fault?
			</li>
			<li >
				If you pay some extra cost can the service provider wave off all the freight costs, if he fails to meet the deadline?
			</li>
			<li >
				Is the service provider equipped for the offshore deliveries? How much do they charge for such deliveries?
			</li>
			<li >
				Do they accept international deliveries?
			</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Be A Freight Dispatcher In Trucking Company</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">Freight dispatchers are mostly employed by different trucking companies for coordinating different shipping 
	operations. A freight dispatcher has the responsibility to pick up the product and then deliver it.  A freight dispatcher prepares the 
	schedule for truck arrivals, pickup and delivery of product and track the work progress for ensuring product delivery on time. They also 
	look after the billing issues with the customers. They carry out the whole truck dispatch service. It includes office work as well as field 
	work.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Steps to become a freight dispatcher</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">Here are some steps which will give you an idea on how to becoming a freight dispatcher-
	<ul>
		<li >
			<b>Earn the associate degree</b> - Some popular trucking companies prefer associate degree holder for freight dispatching work. You can get 
			the knowledge of this work through different courses which include logistics, transportation, import-export management, distribution
			management, economics, etc.
		</li>
		<li >
			<b>Get bachelors degree</b> - Many colleges offer bachelor degree courses for supply chain management, logistics and transportation. 
			If you want to become a well qualified and skilled freight dispatcher, it is better to get the bachelor’s degree along with associate 
			degree.
		</li>
		<li >
			Gain experience- Most freight dispatching companies prefer experienced freight dispatchers. Therefore, you must possess the industry 
			experience. Many companies prefer dispatchers who have trucking experience. A freight dispatcher must possess the knowledge regarding 
			Department of Transportation rules and regulations.
		</li>
	</ul>
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">After getting all the required knowledge and experience, you can be a successful freight dispatcher and you can 
	work in famous trucking companies. You can earn a handsome salary through this work.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>The Experts Of Trucking Dispatch Have Lots Of Responsibilities</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The trucking business depends on safe or experienced drivers for completing the deliveries. It is obviously true 
	that if there is no driver, then the deliveries may not be possible easily. However, if there is no dispatcher, then the drivers may be confused 
	in doing their job. The job of the dispatcher is to arrange the drivers of the truck to lift up or transport loads to the vendors or the customers. 
	For this reason, the trucking dispatch services are becoming popular. You can get more information here.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>The duties of the trucking dispatchers</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The qualified dispatchers may be able to set you up straight with any brokers, shippers or the factories. 
	The trucking dispatch firm will carry out all the required formalities. You will deal with a number of brokers and shippers directly. 
	Moreover, the agents of the firm will observe the several load boards in order to locate your reefer loads or dry freight. The best service 
	providers will help you to keep on working; you will never need to leave the trailers stuck for many days.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The trucking dispatchers are found to be highly responsible for maintaining records and also checking the driver's 
	daily records for any violations or errors. Another job that is done by the dispatchers is to know the weather conditions of the drivers locations.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">Many of the companies will personalize and modify their logistics as well as the truck dispatch solutions just for 
	your requirements. They offer you all the services- from simple truck dispatching to a complete premium dispatch.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Hiring a Truck for all of Your Transportation Needs</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">When you need a truck dispatch service, there are plenty available and they will be able to help you move anything, 
	regardless of the size or where it needs to you. You can hire various types and sizes of vehicles that will allow you to load different items, 
	so go ahead and check out the different ones that are available. Don't move everything by yourself, especially when you can hire the experts to 
	take care of it all.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Hiring a Vehicle</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">Moving can be a daunting task, especially when you have to do it all on your own and you have plenty of huge items. 
	However, when you hire a truck dispatch service, then they will help you with everything. Not only will they make sure that you have the appropriate 
	sized vehicle for your needs, but they will also make sure that everything is packed on the vehicle in a safe manner. This will ensure that nothing 
	gets damaged during the transportation. Don't even think about doing everything on your own, especially if you have other things to worry about, 
	such as kids, but hire the experts.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The experts will be able to make sure that everything is properly put on the truck and, if required, strapped down. 
	Otherwise, they will make sure that everything is packed in a safe manner to ensure that nothing can be damaged on the trip. Why worry about getting 
	everything on the truck after you've already packed it into boxes when you can let the experts deal with it?
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Independent Truck Dispatcher - A Better Option for the Truck Company To Keep Their Costs Low</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">These days the shift is more towards independent truck dispatchers. Drivers and operators both feel that it is more 
	beneficial to have an independent dispatcher. Even the customers are happy with the personalised service that they offer.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>Benefits of Independent Truck Dispatcher:</strong></p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The truck dispatch service is used most often to deliver goods for one place to the other. For timely delivery, 
	a lot of coordination is required besides the heavy-duty stuff like loading and unloading. Many companies have traffic managers and logistics 
	co-coordinator to manage all the independent despatchers. They are in constant touch with the despatchers to ensure that the freight reaches 
	the destination on time and in perfect condition.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The truck despatch service company will also have a daily reporting for shipment location and will help out the 
	independent despatchers in case they face any problems during transportation.
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs"><strong>The reasons for the growing demand on independent despatchers are:</strong>
		<ul>
			<li >
				It keeps the operating cost of the truck company to the minimum.
			</li>
			<li >
				In case of a slack in business, they can still sustain, as they have to pay less number of employees.
			</li>
			<li >
				Fewer in-house employees mean a lesser spending on infrastructure and maintenance.
			</li>
			<li >
				The truckers can also easily shift from one company to the other based on the better deals.
			</li>
			<li >
				Invoicing and book keeping is handled by the trucking company keeping the drivers free from all the office work
			</li>
			<li >
				Customers have a one-point contact, the co-ordinator manager, to find out the status of their goods. This gives 
				them a sense of confidence.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</p>
	
	<p class="g-font-size-18--xs">The idea of the truck company is to give the best services to the customers at the best rates. 
	If the costs are low, the benefits can be passed on to the customers in the form of better rates to create a loyal customer base.
	</p>
